value: London : Printed for I. Walsh in Catharine Street in the Strand, [approximately 1754]

Overture and 15 arias from the opera.
Words after a libretto by Aurelio Aureli and Ortensio Mauro.
HWV 22.
All numbers have additional pagination from earlier publications.
Italian words.
Staff notation.
Founder's bequest, 1816. Inscribed on title page: "R. Fitzwilliam, 1767". 
Received stab stitched in paper covers. Bound in quarter Morocco leather Cockerell paper sides and vellum tips by the Cockerell Bindery in 1980. 
Former shelf numbers: 31.F.18 & x.2.58(a). 

Contents:
Overture in Admetus -- [9] Cangio d'aspetto : Sung by Sigr. Senesino in Admetus -- [10] Un lampo e la speranza : Sung by Sigr. Senesino in Admetus -- [12] Se l'arco avessi e i strali : Sung by Sigr. Baldi in Admetus -- [13] Se'n vola lo sparvier : Sung by Sigra. Cuzzoni in Admetus -- [20] E per monti e per piano : Sung by Sigra. Cuzzoni in Admetus -- [21] Spartite [oh] pensieri : Sung by Sigr. Senesino in Admetus -- [22] Da tanti affanni oppressa : Sung by Sigra. Cuzzoni in Admetus -- [23] Gelosia spietata alletto [=Aletto] : Sung by Sigra. Faustina in Admetus -- [24] Ah si morro : Sung by Sigr. Senesino in Admetus -- [28] Vedro fra poco se l'idodo mio : Sung by Sigra. Faustina in Admetus -- [5b] Spera si mio caro bene : Sung by Sigra. Faustina in Admetus -- [31] La tigre arde di sdegno : Sung by Sigr. Senesino in Admetus -- [33] Io ti bacio oh bella inmago [=imago] : Sung by Sigra. Cuzzoni in Admetus -- [34] La dove gli occhi io giro : Sung by Sigra. Faustina Admetus -- [38] Si caro si : Sung by Sigra. Strada.
The favourite songs in the opera of Admeto / by Mr. Handel.
